- A **dual-branch architecture** that separates pose-aware features from canonicalized shape representations, enabling pose-invariant 3D reconstruction.  
- Use of **self-supervised pose estimation** and **differentiable geometric alignment** to normalize input views before encoding, facilitating invariance.  
- Integration of **view-equivariant constraints** and **rendering-augmented cycle consistency** for improved generalization without requiring multi-view ground truth.  
- Emphasis on **evaluating both reconstruction quality and pose invariance**, with metrics assessing latent stability under rotation.  

This approach aims to enhance robustness in single-view 3D reconstruction for real-world, arbitrary object poses.
